Recall Julia snippets:
- DataFrame creation: `DataFrame(manufacturer = ["audi", "bmw"], model = ["a4", "320i"])`
- Rows filtering: `df[df.manufacturer .== "audi", :]`
- Appending a column: `df.audi_a4_type = trues(size(df, 1))`

Solve the Task:

```julia
using DataFrames

function audi_filter(df_cars)
    df_audi = df_cars[df_cars.manufacturer .== "audi" .&& (df_cars.model .== "a4" .| df_cars.model .== "a4 quattro"), :]
    df_audi.audi_a4_type = trues(size(df_audi, 1))
    return df_audi
end
```

Double-check that the solution is correct:

```julia
df_cars = DataFrame(manufacturer = ["audi", "bmw", "audi"], model = ["a4", "320i", "a4 quattro"])
df_filtered = audi_filter(df_cars)

@assert size(df_filtered, 1) == 2
@assert df_filtered.manufacturer[1] == "audi"
@assert df_filtered.model[1] == "a4"
@assert df_filtered.audi_a4_type[1]
@assert df_filtered.manufacturer[2] == "audi"
@assert df_filtered.model[2] == "a4 quattro"
@assert df_filtered.audi_a4_type[2]
```

The solution is correct.
